Senator Dino Melaye has been handcuffed on his hospital bed by the Nigeria police after he was re-arrested at Zankli hospital Mabushi in Abuja. Melaye who was alleged to have jumped off the moving police vehicle enroute Lokoja was admitted at Zankli hospital when an ambulance brought him and was wheeled on a stretcher into the emergence ward of the hospital. Few hours later over 30 armed policemen led by the Police Force Public Relations OfficerÂ  (PFPRO), Jimoh Moshood surrounded the premises of the hospital to effect his arrest. He was later moved to the National hospital where he is recuperating. Unconfirmed report suggest that the doctor who treated him at the Zankli hospital has been arrested. It was gathered that the doctor claimed that the senator sustained spinal cord injury. 1 comments